+# Why CVE-2025-68972 Does Not Affect gnupg2 in Debian Bullseye
+
+## Overview
+
+Debian Bullseye ships **gnupg2** version **2.2.27** (2.2.x branch). This note
+documents why **CVE-2025-68972** does not apply to this package and no code
+patch is required.
+
+***
+
+## What Is CVE-2025-68972?
+
+CVE-2025-68972 is a cleartext-signature plaintext injection issue tied to
+GnuPG's use of the form-feed character (`\f`) as a marker for truncated
+overlong lines during armor processing. An adversary can construct a modified
+clearsigned message that still verifies while appearing to contain additional
+unsigned text. See https://gpg.fail/formfeed.
+
+The vulnerable behavior was introduced by upstream commit
+`976e9d608367f481f21ab13ec6125dc8ab3ad345` (2022-11-10, GnuPG-bug-id T6272):
+
+* `g10/armor.c` (`fake_packet`): on truncated lines, replace the EOL with
+  `\f` instead of `\n` so truncation is propagated into the hashed plaintext.
+
+That change landed in the **2.4.x** line (present in GnuPG 2.4.0+). It was
+**never backported to the 2.2.x stable branch**.
+
+***
+
+## Why Bullseye gnupg2 (2.2.27) Is Not Affected
+
+| Check | Result |
+|-------|--------|
+| **Shipped version** | `2.2.27-2+deb11u2` (upstream 2.2.27) |
+| **Vulnerable code** | `this_truncated` / `\f` EOL marker in `g10/armor.c` |
+| **Present in 2.2.27?** | **No** — EOL canonicalization always appends `\n` |
+| **Present in 2.2.x tip?** | **No** — still absent in 2.2.41 / 2.2.43 |
+| **Debian packaging** | No debian patch backports commit `976e9d608` |
+| **Affected upstream** | GnuPG **2.4.x** through 2.4.8 (form-feed truncation path) |
+
+### Verification (bullseye source)
+
+```bash
+grep -n "this_truncated" g10/armor.c          # empty
+grep -n "this_truncated? '\\\\f'" g10/armor.c # empty
+# EOL handling still uses plain newline:
+#   afx->buffer[afx->buffer_len++] = '\\n';
+```
+
+Without the form-feed truncation marker, the attack described for this CVE
+cannot be constructed against bullseye's armor filter.
+
+### Conclusion
+
+- **CVE-2025-68972 does not affect** gnupg2 on Debian Bullseye.
+- **No functional code patch is required**; this folder documents the
+  not-affected assessment for scanners / audit trails.
+- Ubuntu jammy (also 2.2.27) reached the same not-affected conclusion.
+
+***
+
+## References
+
+- Advisory write-up: https://gpg.fail/formfeed
+- Introducing commit: https://github.com/gpg/gnupg/commit/976e9d608367f481f21ab13ec6125dc8ab3ad345
+- Debian tracker: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2025-68972
+- NVD: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-68972
+- GnuPG position on cleartext-signature reports:
+  https://gnupg.org/blog/20251226-cleartext-signatures.html
